controls.name: ST_P1_DESC
controls.text: Before scanning the repository, verify that the following have been done:

controls.name: CHK_P1_BACKUP
controls.text: A recent backup is available for this system

controls.name: CHK_P1_MIRROR
controls.text: Repository mirroring is disabled (REVIMAGE.EXE)

controls.name: CHK_P1_USERS
controls.text: All other users are logged out of this system.

controls.name: ST_P1_DESC2
controls.text: The following users are currently logged into this system:

controls.name: ST_P2_DESC
controls.text: All repository entities must have a type and an optional class.  This step in the repository scan checks for the system-defined types and classes and creates any missing ones.

radio-buttons.label: Create known repository types and classes
Do not scan the repository types and classes

controls.name: ST_P2_DESC2
controls.text: To skip this step, select the second option, "Do not scan the repository types and classes".  It is strongly suggested that this scan be performed at least once to ensure that all potential types and classes exist.

controls.name: ST_P3_DESC
controls.text: Select the desired scanning options from the following list:

controls.name: CHK_P3_KEYS
controls.text: Scan repository keys only

controls.name: CHK_P3_USES
controls.text: Validate "uses" dependencies

controls.name: CHK_P3_USEDBY
controls.text: Validate "used by" dependencies

controls.name: CHK_P3_DOCS
controls.text: Validate documentation dependencies

controls.name: CHK_P3_EVENTS
controls.text: Scan for orphaned event handlers

controls.name: CHK_P3_BODY
controls.text: Scan for missing entity bodies

controls.name: CHK_P3_STRICT
controls.text: Use strict validation criteria for entity IDs

controls.name: TEXT_11
controls.text: To begin the full repository scan, press the Next button.  No entities will be deleted without your explicit approval.

controls.name: ST_P4_DESC
controls.text: The repository scan has determined that the following entities may be invalid based on the supplied options.  Carefully select the entities from the list below to delete:

controls.name: CB_P4_SELALL
controls.text: Select All

controls.name: CB_P4_SELNONE
controls.text: Deselect All

controls.name: CB_P4_SORT
controls.text: Sort By ...

controls.name: ST_P5_DESC
controls.text: This is an ordered log of all changes to the repository:

columns.label: Click on a description to zoom

controls.name: ST_P6_DESC
controls.text: The repository scan is complete.  Follow the steps below to ensure system integrity:

controls.name: ST_P6_DESC2
controls.text: 1.  It is possible for invalid repository data to cause system index problems.  Execute the Rebuild System Index option from the Development menu in the Application Manager.

controls.name: ST_P6_DESC3
controls.text: 2.  Consider using repository mirroring, which maintains a second copy of the SYSREPOS table.  To install mirroring, run the REVIMAGE.EXE program in the OpenInsight directory.  For more information, see the OpenInsight white paper titled "Repository Mirroring".

controls.name: ST_P6_DESC4
controls.text: 3.  Use this tool to scan the repository before attempting to deploy an application or upgrade, since invalid repository entries can prevent a successful deployment.
